We can model this problem using the formula
\[20000 \cdot 1.01^3 > 66200.\]We can start by solving for the interest rate in decimal form. Dividing both sides by 20000, we get $1.01^3 > 331$. Taking the natural logarithm of both sides, we get
\[3\ln(1.01) > \ln(331).\]Then $\ln(1.01) > \frac{3}{3} \cdot \ln(331) = \ln(331^\frac{3}{3}) = \ln(331) = 5.81$.
Now, taking the exponent of both sides to the 10th power gives us $1.01^{\! \!10} \approx 1.1046$. (We can check that $1.1046 > 1.01$.) This means that $1.01 \approx 1 + \frac{1}{10} = 1.1$, so the minimal interest rate is $\boxed{10\%}$.

